===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|knitten}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|cnyttan||to fasten, tie, bind, knit; add, append}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*knutjaną}}, {{m|gem-pro|*knuttijaną||to make knots, knit}}. Cognate with Old Norse {{m|non|knýta}} (Danish {{m|da|knytte}}), (Norwegian Nynorsk {{m|nn|knyta}}) and Northern German {{m|de|knütten}}. More at {{l|en|knot}}.

